Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Sandwich each @British Chicken Breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{}. Pop onto a #cutting board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2 cm thick. Season with @salt and @ground black pepper.

Crack the @Egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. Put the @Breadcrumbs{50%grams} and half the @Dried Oregano{1%sachet} into another #bowl{}, season with @Salt for the Breadcrumbs{1/4%tsp} and pepper.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of the pan. TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for ~{2-3%minutes} before you add the chicken. Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Discard the oil from the chicken pan.

== Tomato Spaghetti ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the @Spaghetti{180%grams} to the @Water for the Sauce{150%ml} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Sauce ==

Clean out the chicken pan, then pop it back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil.

Once hot, add the garlic and stir fry for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the remaining oregano, @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%grams}, @Sun-Dried Tomato Paste{25%grams}, @Sugar for the Sauce{1%tsp} and water for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then simmer until slightly thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

When the sauce has thickened, stir in the cooked pasta, @Butter{20%grams} and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams} until well combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it looks too thick.

== To Serve ==

Once the chicken is cooked, carefully slice into 2cm thick slices.

Divide the tomato spaghetti between your #bowls{} and arrange the chicken slices on top.

Scatter the @Wild Rocket{20%grams} on top. Drizzle over the @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml}.

Enjoy!